.TH "ice_devlink_nvm_snapshot" 9 "ice_devlink_nvm_snapshot" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ice_devlink_nvm_snapshot \- Capture a snapshot of the Shadow RAM contents
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ice_devlink_nvm_snapshot
.BI "(struct devlink *devlink "  ","
.BI "const struct devlink_region_ops *ops "  ","
.BI "struct netlink_ext_ack *extack "  ","
.BI "u8 **data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "devlink" 12
the devlink instance
.IP "ops" 12
the devlink region being snapshotted
.IP "extack" 12
extended ACK response structure
.IP "data" 12
on exit points to snapshot data buffer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is called in response to the DEVLINK_CMD_REGION_TRIGGER for
the shadow-ram devlink region. It captures a snapshot of the shadow ram
contents. This snapshot can later be viewed via the devlink-region
interface.

\fIreturns\fP zero on success, and updates the data pointer. Returns a non-zero
error code on failure.
